Diagnosis. Male abdominal sternum 5 with three long setae at each posterolateral angle; surstylus short, thin and pointed. Female abdominal tergum 7 with a V-notch at posterior margin; sternum 7 reduced and composed of two prebasal longitudinal plates (for complete redescription see
Marques & Ale-Rocha 2005
).
